Emma: Earlier, those three fairies tricked him right into a pit... and that's how he got dirty.  #line:ch3_FairyForest_36

Rosé: You guys are really stupid....  #line:ch3_FairyForest_37
Rosé:Anyways, what I really want to ask is why are you guys here? What are you guys doing here, stuck in a pit? I thought you didn't have any more regrets about the Fairy Forest? Are you so stupid you can't even remember what you said? I wonder if you have any common sense to explain what this is all about?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_38

Emma: I knew it... I knew she would tsk tsk tsk us…  #line:ch3_FairyForest_39

Rosé: I beg your pardon?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_40

Emma: Yea, it was nothing…  #line:ch3_FairyForest_41
Emma: Say Rosé, We really wanted to ask something of Lady Frecia, the chief of the fairy forest, so we came to the Fairy Forest again. Well...I know it's going to be a nuisance for everyone, but...it's really important.  #line:ch3_FairyForest_42

Rosé: Well... what is it that you want to ask for?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_43

Emma: I heard that there is a law in the fairy forest that allows you to freely manipulate the wind and run through the sky, and I would like to learn it from Lady Frecia. I was told we needed it for our journey.... I had no idea such a thing existed in the Fairy Forest, do you know anything about this law?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_44


Rosé: The law of running in the sky...?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_45
Rosé: No, I've never heard of such a thing either.   #line:ch3_FairyForest_46

Emma: What? Really? I see! You don't know either! Well, that's good!  #line:ch3_FairyForest_47

Rosé: Huh? What are you looking so happy about?  #line:ch3_FairyForest_48

Emma: No, no, nothing!  #line:ch3_FairyForest_49
